<dl id="n10031j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10031j">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10031j"> 31(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> position ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On appelait <i>Veredi</i> les chevaux de poste, dont il y avait des relais ou stations (<i>positiones</i>), dispos&eacute;es sur les grandes routes ou voies (<i>via</i>), admirablement bien entretenues. <font color="green">[The horses for the post were called <i>Veredi</i>, for whom there were well-maintained relays or stations (<i>positiones</i>), laid out on the large roads or routes (<i>via</i>).]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 29</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
